1
00:00:06,298 --> 00:00:08,801
LOOKS LIKE WE'RE GOING
ABOUT WARP 4.5.

2
00:00:08,843 --> 00:00:10,803
PHLOX: HUMAN CHILDREN HAVE
SUCH FERTILE IMAGINATIONS.

3
00:00:10,845 --> 00:00:13,973
TUCKER: MM.
PHLOX: SUBCOMMANDER.

4
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,891
TUCKER: THESE WERE SENT BY
MY NEPHEW'S FOURTH-GRADE CLASS.

5
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:17,309
I THOUGHT THE CREW
MIGHT LIKE TO SEE

6
00:00:17,351 --> 00:00:19,728
HOW EXCITED FOLKS BACK HOME ARE
ABOUT OUR MISSION.

7
00:00:19,770 --> 00:00:21,814
PHLOX: YEAH, I'M GOING TO PUT
THIS ONE UP IN SICK BAY.

8
00:00:21,856 --> 00:00:23,858
WOULD YOU LIKE ONE
FOR YOUR QUARTERS?

9
00:00:23,899 --> 00:00:27,027
T'POL: THIS RENDERING IS CRUDE,
YET SURPRISINGLY ACCURATE.

10
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:29,905
TUCKER: HUH. SOME OF THESE KIDS
ARE PRETTY TALENTED.

11
00:00:29,947 --> 00:00:31,991
WHICH ONE DO YOU WANT?

12
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:34,409
THIS ONE'S NICE.

13
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:38,413
OR...MAYBE YOU WANT
FIRST CONTACT?

14
00:00:39,790 --> 00:00:43,335
OR...HOW ABOUT THIS ONE?

15
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:48,924
[ ENGINES WHOOSH ]

16
00:00:48,966 --> 00:00:50,634
T'POL: WE'RE
DROPPING OUT OF WARP.

17
00:00:50,676 --> 00:00:52,928
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:54,429
[ BEEP ]

19
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:55,973
ARCHER:<i> FOR THOSE OF YOU</i>
<i>WHO AREN'T NEAR A WINDOW,</i>

20
00:00:56,015 --> 00:00:57,474
<i>YOU MIGHT WANT TO FIND ONE.</i>

21
00:00:57,516 --> 00:00:59,643
<i>THERE'S SOMETHING</i>
<i>PRETTY AMAZING OFF STARBOARD.</i>

22
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:07,317
ARCHER: SENIOR STAFF,
PLEASE REPORT TO THE BRIDGE.

23
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:09,444
REED: I'VE CHECKED
THE VULCAN DATABASE, SIR.

24
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:10,738
NO PREVIOUS SIGHTINGS.

25
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:12,031
THAT MEANS WE DISCOVERED IT.

26
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:15,075
TRAVIS: ARCHER'S COMET.

27
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:17,036
TAKE US CLOSER, ENSIGN.

28
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:18,495
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

29
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:35,763
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

30
00:01:35,804 --> 00:01:39,016
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

31
00:01:39,058 --> 00:01:42,853
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

32
00:01:42,895 --> 00:01:46,565
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

33
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:51,028
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

34
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:54,656
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

35
00:01:54,698 --> 00:01:58,660
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

36
00:01:58,702 --> 00:02:01,496
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

37
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:05,000
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

38
00:02:05,042 --> 00:02:06,460
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

39
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:10,047
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

40
00:02:10,089 --> 00:02:15,052
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

41
00:02:15,094 --> 00:02:17,304
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

42
00:02:17,345 --> 00:02:22,183
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

43
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:25,062
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

44
00:02:25,104 --> 00:02:30,609
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

45
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,611
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

46
00:02:32,653 --> 00:02:35,030
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

47
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:38,283
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

48
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:43,204
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

49
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:01,849
ARCHER: EVER SEEN ANYTHING LIKE
THAT IN YOUR ASTRONOMY BOOKS?

50
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,391
TUCKER: WOW!

51
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:05,644
[ ARCHER CHUCKLES ]
TUCKER: THAT'S ONE BIG SNOWBALL.

52
00:03:05,686 --> 00:03:09,439
THE DIAMETER IS 82.6 KILOMETERS.

53
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:11,525
ARCHER: I ALWAYS WANTED
TO CHASE A COMET.

54
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:14,653
MAYBE WE SHOULD SPEND A FEW DAYS
FOLLOWING THIS ONE.

55
00:03:14,695 --> 00:03:16,613
T'POL: VULCAN
AND HUMAN SCIENTISTS

56
00:03:16,655 --> 00:03:18,490
HAVE RESEARCHED HUNDREDS
OF COMETS.

57
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:21,242
THEY'VE PROVEN TO BE
LITTLE MORE THAN ROCK AND ICE.

58
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:24,705
ARCHER: EXCEPT
THIS ONE'S BIGGER THAN

59
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,915
ANY COMET HUMANS
HAVE EVER SEEN.

60
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:29,710
NOW, THAT'S GOT TO BE
WORTH A LOOK.

61
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:31,210
STAY WITH IT, TRAVIS.

62
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:32,504
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

63
00:04:06,038 --> 00:04:07,247
MMM!

64
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:16,297
TUCKER: MILK. COLD.

65
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:21,053
TUCKER: CATCHING UP
ON YOUR READING?

66
00:04:21,095 --> 00:04:22,512
T'POL: I CAME FOR TEA.

67
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:24,598
TUCKER: WELL, STAY AWAY FROM
THE ZARIPHEAN BLEND,

68
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:27,226
UNLESS YOU WANT TO STAY UP
FOR THE NEXT 3 DAYS.

69
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:30,604
T'POL: CAFFEINE HAS LITTLE
EFFECT ON VULCAN PHYSIOLOGY.

70
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,981
GREEN TEA, HOT.

71
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:41,073
TUCKER: YOU WANT TO JOIN ME?
I COULD USE THE COMPANY.

72
00:04:41,115 --> 00:04:42,574
T'POL: I'M VERY TIRED.

73
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:44,243
TUCKER: TELL ME ABOUT IT.

74
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:46,828
PUT OUT ABOUT A HUNDRED FIRES
IN ENGINEERING THIS AFTERNOON

75
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,122
AND MISSED DINNER.

76
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:50,124
THEN SOMEBODY TOLD ME
CHEF MADE A PECAN PIE,

77
00:04:50,165 --> 00:04:51,875
AND SUDDENLY,
MY LIFE BRIGHTENED.

78
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:56,255
IT'S BEEN MY FAVORITE
SINCE I WAS A KID.

79
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:58,173
CARE FOR A BITE?

80
00:04:58,215 --> 00:04:59,258
T'POL: NO, THANK YOU.

81
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:00,300
TUCKER: IT'S DELICIOUS.

82
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:01,593
T'POL: IT'S MOSTLY SUGAR.

83
00:05:01,635 --> 00:05:03,887
WELL, VULCANS
DON'T HAVE A SWEET TOOTH?

84
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:08,142
MAY NOT BE GOOD FOR THE BODY,

85
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:10,644
BUT IT SURE IS GOOD
FOR THE SOUL.

86
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:16,316
MMM!

87
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:19,319
I FEEL BETTER ALREADY.

88
00:05:21,362 --> 00:05:23,531
TUCKER: MUST BE
A REAL PAGE-TURNER.

89
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:29,329
YOU ALL RIGHT?

90
00:05:31,290 --> 00:05:34,001
I'M FINE, COMMANDER.

91
00:05:34,042 --> 00:05:35,543
GOOD NIGHT.

92
00:05:37,378 --> 00:05:39,173
TUCKER: SWEET DREAMS.

93
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:48,015
ARCHER: EISILIUM?

94
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,891
T'POL: IT'S AN EXTREMELY
RARE MINERAL.

95
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:53,061
THIS COMET APPEARS TO CONTAIN
LARGE QUANTITIES OF IT.

96
00:05:53,103 --> 00:05:54,896
ARCHER: I'VE NEVER
HEARD OF EISILIUM.

97
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:57,191
T'POL: VULCAN CHEMISTS HAVE
ONLY OBTAINED SMALL AMOUNTS.

98
00:05:57,232 --> 00:05:59,318
THEY'VE NEVER BEEN ABLE
TO STUDY IT IN DETAIL.

99
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:01,153
ARCHER: THIS COULD
BE YOUR CHANCE.

100
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:03,864
CAN WE COLLECT A SAMPLE
WITH THE TRANSPORTER?

101
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,448
T'POL: MOST OF
THE EISILIUM DEPOSITS

102
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,617
ARE AT LEAST 20 METERS
BENEATH THE CRUST.

103
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:09,536
TUCKER: THAT'S TOO DEEP
TO GET A LOCK.

104
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:11,663
REED: WE'VE GOT THE PORTABLE
DRILLING RIG, SIR.

105
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:13,999
TRAVIS: THE COMET'S CERTAINLY
BIG ENOUGH TO LAND ON.

106
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,917
WE COULD TAKE A SHUTTLEPOD.

107
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:18,920
T'POL: I'D ADVISE SETTING DOWN
NEAR ONE OF THE TWO POLES.

108
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:20,630
IF YOU'RE OUT
OF DIRECT SUNLIGHT,

109
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:22,716
THE SURFACE ICE
WILL BE MORE STABLE.

110
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:24,176
HOW LONG WOULD YOU NEED?

111
00:06:24,218 --> 00:06:26,385
REED: SHOULDN'T TAKE MORE
THAN 3 OR 4 HOURS.

112
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:28,387
YOU UP FOR A LITTLE COMET WALK?

113
00:06:29,681 --> 00:06:31,683
REED: BY ALL MEANS.

114
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:34,435
ARCHER: GET STARTED.

115
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:37,272
CAPTAIN,

116
00:06:37,314 --> 00:06:40,608
I'M DETECTING A VESSEL
CLOSING ON OUR POSITION.

117
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,694
IT'S VULCAN.

118
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:46,156
THE STARSHIP<i> TI'MUR.</i>

119
00:06:46,198 --> 00:06:47,782
ARCHER: HAIL THEM.

120
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:54,289
THIS IS CAPTAIN JONATHAN ARCHER
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

121
00:06:54,331 --> 00:06:56,208
<i>VULCAN: I'M CAPTAIN VANIK.</i>

122
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,792
ARCHER: PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

123
00:06:57,834 --> 00:07:00,128
<i>YOU'RE A LONG WAY</i>
<i>FROM EARTH, CAPTAIN.</i>

124
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:01,671
<i>ARE YOU LOST?</i>

125
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:06,509
ARCHER: NOT AT ALL. JUST TAKING
A LOOK AT THIS COMET.

126
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:09,428
<i>OUR SENSORS DETECTED IT</i>
<i>TWO DAYS AGO.</i>

127
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:12,349
<i>WE ALSO DECIDED TO INVESTIGATE.</i>

128
00:07:12,391 --> 00:07:13,975
ARCHER: REALLY?

129
00:07:14,017 --> 00:07:16,395
MY SCIENCE OFFICER TELLS ME

130
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:19,106
THAT VULCANS AREN'T
VERY INTERESTED IN COMETS.

131
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:21,649
<i>ACTUALLY, IT'S YOUR INTEREST</i>
<i>IN THE COMET</i>

132
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:23,193
<i>WE'RE INVESTIGATING.</i>

133
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:27,030
ARCHER: WE PLAN TO SEND
A DRILLING TEAM TO THE SURFACE

134
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:29,408
TO COLLECT CORE SAMPLES.

135
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,410
YOU'RE WELCOME TO PARTICIPATE.

136
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:33,036
<i>IF YOU HAVE NO OBJECTION,</i>

137
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:35,372
<i>WE'D LIKE TO REMAIN HERE</i>
<i>AND OBSERVE.</i>

138
00:07:35,414 --> 00:07:37,791
STAY AS LONG AS YOU WANT.

139
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:43,504
ARCHER: T'POL.

140
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:56,017
I'D LOVE TO KNOW
WHAT THEY'RE REALLY DOING HERE.

141
00:07:57,227 --> 00:07:59,020
YOU DON'T FIND ANYTHING STRANGE

142
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:01,148
ABOUT THEM SUDDENLY
SHOWING UP?

143
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:03,483
T'POL: PERHAPS THEY'RE
SIMPLY CURIOUS.

144
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:05,193
ARCHER: CURIOUS?

145
00:08:05,235 --> 00:08:07,988
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
VERY VULCAN TO ME.

146
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,990
THIS ISN'T THE FIRST TIME

147
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:12,409
WE'VE CAUGHT THEM
LURKING AROUND.

148
00:08:12,451 --> 00:08:16,121
REMEMBER 3 WEEKS AGO,
THE PLANETARY NEBULA?

149
00:08:16,163 --> 00:08:18,623
T'POL: THAT WAS NOTHING MORE
THAN A SURVEY SHIP.

150
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:20,792
ARCHER: SO WHY DIDN'T THEY
RESPOND TO OUR HAILS?

151
00:08:20,834 --> 00:08:23,462
WHY'D THEY GO TO WARP
WHEN WE HEADED TOWARD THEM?

152
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:25,505
I'M STARTING TO GET THE FEELING

153
00:08:25,546 --> 00:08:28,883
THEY'RE LOOKING OVER
OUR SHOULDER A LITTLE TOO OFTEN.

154
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,885
THAT SEEMS UNLIKELY.

155
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,096
ARCHER: WE'LL SEE.

156
00:08:33,138 --> 00:08:34,514
FINE.

157
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:40,479
IF VANIK IS THE KIND OF GUY
WHO LIKES TO WATCH...

158
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,272
LET HIM.

159
00:08:55,494 --> 00:08:58,788
I'VE NEVER STOOD
ON A COMET BEFORE.

160
00:08:58,830 --> 00:09:00,374
TRAVIS: HAS ANYONE?

161
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:02,501
REED: GOOD QUESTION.

162
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:05,212
TRAVIS: I'VE ONLY SEEN SNOW
TWICE IN MY LIFE.

163
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:06,505
WELL, THEN IT'S ONLY FITTING

164
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:08,465
THAT WE COMMEMORATE
THE OCCASION.

165
00:09:08,507 --> 00:09:09,799
YOU MEAN PLANT A FLAG?

166
00:09:09,841 --> 00:09:11,510
REED: NAH, TOO PREDICTABLE.

167
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:12,886
SNOWBALL FIGHT.

168
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:16,181
THE E.V. SUITS WOULD TAKE
ALL THE FUN OUT OF THAT.

169
00:09:16,223 --> 00:09:19,351
EH, WE'LL JUST HAVE TO SEE
HOW THE SPIRIT MOVES US

170
00:09:19,393 --> 00:09:20,852
WHEN WE GET THERE.

171
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,226
HOSHI: COMMANDER,
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

172
00:10:01,268 --> 00:10:03,228
TUCKER: TAKE A LOOK AT
SOMETHING, WILL YOU?

173
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:05,146
I'VE BEEN RUNNING DIAGNOSTICS,

174
00:10:05,188 --> 00:10:07,566
AND I FOUND
SOME KIND OF POWER SURGE

175
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,109
IN THE TRANSCEIVER ARRAY.

176
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:11,445
HOSHI: LOOKS LIKE
AN ENCRYPTED TRANSMISSION.

177
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:19,660
HOSHI: IT CAME FROM
THE VULCAN SHIP.

178
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:21,662
TUCKER: WHO WAS IT SENT TO?

179
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:27,586
ARCHER: YOU'RE SURE THIS WAS
SENT TO HER QUARTERS?

180
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:29,003
TUCKER: I WISH I WASN'T.

181
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,548
DID SHE SAY ANYTHING TO YOU
ABOUT IT?

182
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:33,633
NOT A WORD.

183
00:10:33,674 --> 00:10:36,761
WE HAD AN AGREEMENT.

184
00:10:36,803 --> 00:10:39,431
SHE PROMISED NOT
TO SPEAK TO THE VULCANS

185
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:40,681
WITHOUT TELLING ME.

186
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:43,477
LOOKS LIKE SHE'S HAVING
SOME TROUBLE

187
00:10:43,518 --> 00:10:45,270
KEEPING HER PROMISES.

188
00:10:45,312 --> 00:10:46,938
SHOULD I HAVE HOSHI DECRYPT IT?

189
00:10:50,942 --> 00:10:53,820
TELL HER IT'S TOP PRIORITY.

190
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,871
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY, CAPTAIN.

191
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:06,749
TUCKER: YOU SURE YOU
WANT ME HERE FOR THIS?

192
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,709
I'VE GOT A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

193
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:10,420
STAY PUT, COMMANDER.

194
00:11:10,462 --> 00:11:12,088
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

195
00:11:17,718 --> 00:11:21,640
ARCHER: START THE RECORDING.

196
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:25,268
TO THE STUDENTS OF MS. MALVIN'S
FOURTH-GRADE CLASS

197
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:27,770
AT THE WORLEY ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

198
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:30,440
IN KENMARE,
COUNTY KERRY, IRELAND,

199
00:11:30,482 --> 00:11:35,236
THIS IS CAPTAIN ARCHER
ABOARD THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

200
00:11:35,278 --> 00:11:37,614
ON BEHALF OF THE ENTIRE CREW,

201
00:11:37,656 --> 00:11:41,284
I'D LIKE TO THANK YOU
FOR YOUR TRANSMISSION.

202
00:11:41,326 --> 00:11:45,205
WE ALL GOT A REAL KICK OUT
OF YOUR DRAWINGS AND LETTERS.

203
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:48,041
YOU ASKED A LOT
OF INTERESTING QUESTIONS.

204
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:50,544
I WISH WE HAD TIME
TO ANSWER ALL OF THEM,

205
00:11:50,585 --> 00:11:53,672
BUT IF WE DID THAT, WE WOULDN'T
GET MUCH EXPLORING DONE.

206
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:56,383
SO I'VE SELECTED A FEW,

207
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,427
AND HOPEFULLY OUR ANSWERS
WILL GIVE YOU A BETTER IDEA

208
00:11:59,469 --> 00:12:02,805
OF WHAT LIFE IS LIKE OUT HERE.

209
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:07,726
LIAM BRENNAN ASKS,
"WHAT DO YOU EAT?"

210
00:12:07,768 --> 00:12:11,856
FOR THE MOST PART,
THE SAME THINGS YOU EAT AT HOME.

211
00:12:11,898 --> 00:12:13,774
OUR CHEF CAN MAKE ANYTHING

212
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:16,110
FROM A PEANUT BUTTER
AND JELLY SANDWICH

213
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:19,113
TO A TURKEY
WITH ALL THE TRIMMINGS.

214
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:22,617
WE HAVE A HYDROPONIC GREENHOUSE
ONBOARD

215
00:12:22,659 --> 00:12:24,244
WHERE WE GROW
FRUITS AND VEGETABLES,

216
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:27,330
AND WE CAN ALSO
REPLICATE CERTAIN FOODS

217
00:12:27,372 --> 00:12:30,124
WITH OUR PROTEIN RESEQUENCER.

218
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,876
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

219
00:12:31,918 --> 00:12:34,713
HERE'S ONE FROM GEOFF MILES.

220
00:12:34,753 --> 00:12:38,717
"IS DATING ALLOWED
ON<i> ENTERPRISE?"</i>

221
00:12:38,757 --> 00:12:41,469
WELL, IT'S NOT DISCOURAGED,

222
00:12:41,511 --> 00:12:44,681
BUT THERE ISN'T A LOT OF PRIVACY
ON A STARSHIP.

223
00:12:44,723 --> 00:12:47,684
MOST OF OUR CREW SHARE QUARTERS
WITH AT LEAST ONE OTHER PERSON,

224
00:12:47,726 --> 00:12:53,607
SO, IT WOULDN'T...
EXACTLY...BE PRACTICAL.

225
00:12:53,648 --> 00:12:55,483
BUT IF TWO CREW MEMBERS

226
00:12:55,525 --> 00:12:57,818
DECIDE THAT THEY REALLY
LIKE EACH OTHER,

227
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:02,365
THERE ARE A LOT OF PLACES THEY
CAN GO TO LOOK AT THE STARS.

228
00:13:02,407 --> 00:13:05,410
CHLOE O'SHANNON
WANTS TO KNOW,

229
00:13:05,452 --> 00:13:07,746
"HOW DO WE TALK TO ALIENS?"

230
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:11,874
I THINK I'LL GIVE THAT ONE
TO MY COMMUNICATIONS OFFICER,

231
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:14,252
ENSIGN HOSHI SATO.

232
00:13:14,294 --> 00:13:17,088
HOSHI: WELL, CHLOE,
THAT'S A VERY GOOD QUESTION.

233
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:20,634
WE USE A DEVICE CALLED
THE UNIVERSAL TRANSLATOR.

234
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:21,968
IT'S LIKE AN ALIEN DICTIONARY

235
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:25,054
WITH HUNDREDS OF LANGUAGES
PROGRAMMED INTO IT,

236
00:13:25,096 --> 00:13:28,057
AND IT CAN LEARN NEW LANGUAGES
VERY QUICKLY.

237
00:13:28,099 --> 00:13:31,185
BUT IT DOESN'T ALWAYS WORK,
AND WHEN THAT HAPPENS,

238
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:33,438
IT'S UP TO ME
TO TRY TO TRANSLATE.

239
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,440
I'M SURE
I DON'T HAVE TO TELL YOU

240
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:37,233
IT CAN BE REALLY
HARD SOMETIMES.

241
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:41,279
ONE WRONG WORD CAN MEAN
THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN SAYING

242
00:13:41,321 --> 00:13:43,782
"TAKE MY HAND"
OR "TAKE MY LIFE."

243
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:46,743
SO FAR I'VE MANAGED
TO DO PRETTY WELL.

244
00:13:46,785 --> 00:13:48,286
ARCHER: THANKS, HOSHI.

245
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:50,829
HERE'S ONE FROM MOLLY McCOOK.

246
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:54,959
"WHEN YOU FLUSH THE TOILET,
WHERE DOES IT GO?"

247
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:58,463
THAT SOUNDS LIKE
AN ENGINEERING QUESTION,

248
00:13:58,505 --> 00:14:04,511
SO WE'LL ASK COMMANDER CHARLES
TUCKER, OUR CHIEF ENGINEER.

249
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:05,844
TRIP?

250
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:08,556
TUCKER: PAUSE IT, WILL YOU?

251
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:13,812
A POOP QUESTION, SIR?

252
00:14:13,852 --> 00:14:17,398
CAN'T I TALK ABOUT THE WARP
REACTOR OR THE TRANSPORTER?

253
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,900
IT'S A PERFECTLY
VALID QUESTION.

254
00:14:24,489 --> 00:14:27,534
FIRST THING
YOU'VE GOT TO UNDERSTAND

255
00:14:27,575 --> 00:14:32,121
IS WE RECYCLE PRETTY MUCH
EVERYTHING ON A STARSHIP.

256
00:14:32,163 --> 00:14:34,290
THAT INCLUDES...WASTE.

257
00:14:34,332 --> 00:14:38,044
UH, THE FIRST THING
THAT HAPPENS TO THE WASTE

258
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,754
IS IT GETS PROCESSED

259
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:43,924
THROUGH A MACHINE CALLED
A BIO-MATTER RESEQUENCER.

260
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:46,886
THEN IT GETS BROKEN DOWN
INTO...

261
00:14:46,927 --> 00:14:48,471
HOLD ON.

262
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:53,017
THEY'RE GONNA THINK
I'M THE SANITATION ENGINEER.

263
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,186
YOU'RE DOING FINE.

264
00:14:58,981 --> 00:15:01,901
SO, THE WASTE IS BROKEN DOWN
INTO LITTLE MOLECULES,

265
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:05,405
AND THEN THEY GET TRANSFORMED
INTO ANY NUMBER OF THINGS

266
00:15:05,446 --> 00:15:06,781
WE CAN USE ON THE SHIP--

267
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:10,910
CARGO CONTAINERS,
INSULATION, BOOTS.

268
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:16,082
TUCKER: YOU NAME IT.

269
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:20,920
ARCHER: VERY ENLIGHTENING,
COMMANDER.

270
00:15:20,961 --> 00:15:25,966
GABRIELLE WITTY WANTS TO KNOW
IF GERMS CAN LIVE IN SPACE.

271
00:15:26,008 --> 00:15:30,722
AH. I BELIEVE I CAN
ANSWER THAT, CAPTAIN.

272
00:15:30,764 --> 00:15:32,056
HELLO, CHILDREN.

273
00:15:32,098 --> 00:15:35,393
I'M DR. PHLOX,
THE SHIP'S PHYSICIAN.

274
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:38,938
I'M FROM A SYSTEM
CALLED DENOBULA TRIAXA,

275
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:42,942
AND I FEEL VERY HONORED TO BE
PART OF THIS IMPORTANT MISSION.

276
00:15:42,983 --> 00:15:44,903
GERMS--MM-HMM.

277
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,654
THEY MAY BE TINY,
BUT THEY ARE AMONG

278
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:49,407
THE MOST RESILIENT ORGANISMS
KNOWN TO MEDICAL SCIENCE.

279
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:51,075
THEY CAN SURVIVE
ALMOST ANYWHERE--

280
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:53,369
ON YOUR KITCHEN COUNTER,
UNDER YOUR FINGERNAIL.

281
00:15:53,411 --> 00:15:57,498
IN THE VACUUM OF SPACE,
OVER 200 MILLION

282
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:00,042
SPACE-DWELLING MICROBES
HAVE BEEN CATALOGED.

283
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,753
ONE OF THE MOST
VIRULENT SPECIES

284
00:16:01,795 --> 00:16:03,963
LIVES INSIDE GRAINS
OF INTERSTELLAR DUST.

285
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:05,465
POLYCOCYX ASTRIS--

286
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:10,010
THEY CAN DRIFT IN A DORMANT
STATE FOR MILLIONS OF YEARS

287
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:12,054
AND STILL CAUSE A NASTY COLD.

288
00:16:12,096 --> 00:16:14,223
[ CHUCKLES ]

289
00:16:14,265 --> 00:16:18,311
I ONCE DISCOVERED
A PECULIAR COLONY OF SPORES

290
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:20,229
PHLOX: ON A, UM, HULL OF A--
ARCHER: THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

291
00:16:20,271 --> 00:16:21,940
FASCINATING.

292
00:16:22,022 --> 00:16:26,694
I THINK WE'VE TAKEN UP ENOUGH
OF MS. MALVIN'S CLASSROOM TIME.

293
00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:28,321
BY THE WAY, WE'VE INCLUDED

294
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:31,699
SOME PICTURES OF A COMET
WE'RE STUDYING.

295
00:16:31,741 --> 00:16:35,286
WE THINK IT MIGHT BE
THE BIGGEST ONE EVER DISCOVERED

296
00:16:35,328 --> 00:16:36,871
BY HUMANS OR VULCANS.

297
00:16:36,913 --> 00:16:39,958
THAT'S WHAT'S SO EXCITING
ABOUT BEING ON<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

298
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:43,837
YOU NEVER KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA FIND NEXT.

299
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:47,841
WE MISS EARTH,
BUT HEARING FROM YOU

300
00:16:47,882 --> 00:16:51,010
MAKES US ALL FEEL
A LITTLE CLOSER TO HOME.

301
00:16:51,051 --> 00:16:54,347
CAPTAIN ARCHER OUT.

302
00:16:56,599 --> 00:16:59,477
[ SIGHS ] HOW'D IT GO?

303
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:05,399
REED: THE BEAUTY OF ICE

304
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:07,568
IS THAT IT RECORDS EVERYTHING
LIKE A BLANK PAGE.

305
00:17:07,610 --> 00:17:12,031
THE FARTHER DOWN YOU DRILL,
THE FARTHER BACK IN TIME YOU GO.

306
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:15,159
TRAVIS: LIEUTENANT?

307
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:16,285
REED: YES?

308
00:17:16,327 --> 00:17:18,955
TRAVIS: WHAT DO YOU THINK?

309
00:17:18,997 --> 00:17:20,373
[ REED LAUGHS ]

310
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:26,587
REED: HAND ME THE PLASMA TORCH.

311
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:45,272
[ LAUGHTER,
COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

312
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,650
ARCHER: ARCHER
TO LIEUTENANT REED.

313
00:17:47,692 --> 00:17:48,651
REED: GO AHEAD, SIR.

314
00:17:48,693 --> 00:17:49,944
ARCHER: HOW YOU DOING, MALCOLM?

315
00:17:49,986 --> 00:17:51,779
REED: WE'RE JUST ABOUT
TO SET THE CHARGES.

316
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:54,657
I'M SURE I DON'T NEED TO REMIND
YOU WE'RE BEING OBSERVED.

317
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:56,075
REED: NO, SIR.

318
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:58,912
ARCHER: WE WANT THIS TO GO
AS SMOOTHLY AS POSSIBLE.

319
00:17:58,953 --> 00:18:00,120
MAKE A GOOD IMPRESSION.

320
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:01,288
REED: RIGHT.

321
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:03,123
ARCHER: SO, TELL ME...

322
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,960
WHO'S THE SCULPTOR?

323
00:18:06,002 --> 00:18:08,546
[ REED CLEARS THROAT ]
IT WON'T BE THERE FOR LONG, SIR.

324
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:11,215
ARCHER OUT.

325
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:16,637
TUCKER: ANY LUCK?

326
00:18:16,679 --> 00:18:19,682
HOSHI: SORRY IT TOOK SO LONG.
THE CODE WAS PRETTY COMPLEX.

327
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:20,641
TUCKER: WHAT'S IT SAY?

328
00:18:20,683 --> 00:18:22,184
HOSHI: IT'S IN VULCAN.

329
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:24,520
YOU'LL HAVE TO RUN IT THROUGH
THE TRANSLATION MATRIX.

330
00:18:24,562 --> 00:18:25,897
TUCKER: YOU DIDN'T READ IT?

331
00:18:25,939 --> 00:18:28,107
HOSHI: I DIDN'T FEEL
IT WOULD BE RIGHT.

332
00:18:28,148 --> 00:18:30,610
TUCKER: [ SIGHS ] THANKS.

333
00:18:45,374 --> 00:18:48,086
[ SIGHS ]

334
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:49,837
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

335
00:18:49,879 --> 00:18:51,839
ARCHER: COME IN.

336
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:56,135
TUCKER: WELL,
WE DECRYPTED THE MESSAGE.

337
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:58,471
ARCHER: AND?

338
00:18:58,512 --> 00:19:03,017
TUCKER: IT'S NOT EXACTLY
WHAT WE EXPECTED.

339
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:04,143
IT'S A LETTER.

340
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:06,104
WHAT DID IT SAY?

341
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,271
TUCKER: IT'S PERSONAL.

342
00:19:07,313 --> 00:19:08,606
ARCHER: WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

343
00:19:08,648 --> 00:19:10,108
TUCKER:<i> VERY</i> PERSONAL.

344
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,859
ARCHER: OH.

345
00:19:11,901 --> 00:19:13,527
TUCKER: YOU COULD ORDER ME
TO TELL YOU, SIR,

346
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,113
BUT YOU WOULDN'T
BE HAPPY IF I DID.

347
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:16,322
ARCHER: WHY THE HELL
WAS IT ENCRYPTED?

348
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:17,782
TUCKER: THAT'S WHAT
I WANT TO KNOW!

349
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:20,868
MAYBE VULCANS ENCRYPT
ALL THEIR PERSONAL LETTERS.

350
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:23,830
ALL THEY HAD TO DO WAS SEND IT
THROUGH REGULAR CHANNELS,

351
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:26,124
MARK IT PERSONAL,
AND WE'D HAVE LEFT IT ALONE,

352
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,208
BUT, NO, THEY HAD
TO ENCRYPT IT,

353
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:29,877
FORCE ME TO START SNOOPING.

354
00:19:29,919 --> 00:19:32,880
I FEEL LIKE I GOT CAUGHT
WITH MY HAND IN THE COOKIE JAR.

355
00:19:32,922 --> 00:19:35,967
ARCHER: LET IT GO, TRIP.

356
00:19:36,009 --> 00:19:38,302
I MEAN, COME ON,
IT WAS AN HONEST MISTAKE.

357
00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:41,139
TUCKER: OH, I CAN'T LET IT GO.

358
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:45,143
I GOT TO TELL HER.

359
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,478
ARCHER: HOW'S THAT GONNA HELP?

360
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,105
TUCKER: IT'S THE RIGHT
THING TO DO.

361
00:19:49,147 --> 00:19:51,774
AT LEAST I'LL BE ABLE
TO LOOK HER IN THE EYE

362
00:19:51,816 --> 00:19:53,233
WITHOUT FEELING GUILTY.

363
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:56,029
[ ARCHER SIGHS ]

364
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:57,780
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN.

365
00:20:01,492 --> 00:20:05,079
YOU MIGHT WANT TO TAKE
A PHASE PISTOL WITH YOU.

366
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:06,873
TUCKER: I MIGHT NEED ONE.

367
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:22,096
TUCKER: GOT A MINUTE?

368
00:20:22,138 --> 00:20:23,222
IN PRIVATE?

369
00:20:23,263 --> 00:20:25,725
T'POL: EXCUSE US, CREWMAN.

370
00:20:31,271 --> 00:20:34,859
TUCKER: DID YOU EVER--

371
00:20:34,901 --> 00:20:38,612
DID YOU EVER DO ANYTHING
TOTALLY BY MISTAKE

372
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:42,616
THAT...YOU WEREN'T
VERY PROUD OF?

373
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:44,869
T'POL: NO.

374
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:50,583
TUCKER: DID YOU EVER...
COME ACROSS SOMETHING

375
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:52,793
THAT--THAT--THAT
YOU THOUGHT WAS ONE THING,

376
00:20:52,835 --> 00:20:55,213
SO YOU REACTED
IN A CERTAIN WAY,

377
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:57,464
BUT THEN IT TURNED OUT TO BE
SOMETHING COMPLETELY DIFFERENT?

378
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,592
T'POL: YOUR POINT, COMMANDER?

379
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,137
[ TUCKER SIGHS ]

380
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:06,599
I FOUND OUT ABOUT YOUR MESSAGE
FROM THE VULCAN SHIP.

381
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:10,728
T'POL: IT WAS
A PERSONAL MATTER.

382
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:11,771
TUCKER: WHY WASN'T IT
SENT THROUGH NORMAL

383
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:13,189
STARFLEET CHANNELS?

384
00:21:13,231 --> 00:21:15,816
T'POL: THAT TAKES TIME.
THE LETTER WAS IMPORTANT.

385
00:21:15,858 --> 00:21:18,236
TUCKER: SO THEY
SENT IT IN CODE?

386
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:22,240
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW SUSPICIOUS THAT LOOKED?

387
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:25,576
T'POL: YOU READ MY LETTER?

388
00:21:25,618 --> 00:21:29,329
TUCKER: BELIEVE ME, I DON'T
FEEL VERY GOOD ABOUT IT.

389
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:31,331
T'POL: I HAVE MORE LETTERS
IN MY QUARTERS.

390
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:33,542
WOULD YOU LIKE TO
READ THOSE AS WELL?

391
00:21:33,584 --> 00:21:35,253
[ TUCKER SIGHS ]

392
00:21:35,294 --> 00:21:38,131
I'M TRYING TO APOLOGIZE HERE.
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

393
00:21:38,172 --> 00:21:40,091
ARCHER: ARCHER TO T'POL.

394
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:41,341
T'POL: YES, CAPTAIN?

395
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:45,263
ARCHER: PLEASE REPORT
TO MY READY ROOM.

396
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:47,306
T'POL: HAS ANYONE ELSE
READ THE LETTER?

397
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:49,183
TUCKER: NO.

398
00:21:49,225 --> 00:21:53,229
T'POL: I'D APPRECIATE IT
IF YOU WOULDN'T MENTION IT.

399
00:21:53,271 --> 00:21:56,023
TUCKER: I WON'T.
I PROMISE.

400
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:04,740
I THOUGHT I'D INVITE
CAPTAIN VANIK FOR A VISIT.

401
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:07,910
IF HE'S SO INTERESTED
IN HOW WE DO THINGS,

402
00:22:07,952 --> 00:22:10,830
HE MIGHT AS WELL
COME SEE FOR HIMSELF.

403
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:15,293
ONCE HE REALIZES WE'RE NOT GONNA
BLOW UP THE GALAXY,

404
00:22:15,334 --> 00:22:17,211
MAYBE HE'LL LEAVE US ALONE.

405
00:22:17,253 --> 00:22:19,130
I'M SURE
HE'LL APPRECIATE THE GESTURE.

406
00:22:19,172 --> 00:22:21,882
DINNER'S A GOOD WAY
TO BREAK THE ICE.

407
00:22:21,924 --> 00:22:26,304
I WAS HOPING YOU MIGHT GIVE CHEF
SOME MENU SUGGESTIONS.

408
00:22:26,344 --> 00:22:27,387
T'POL: CERTAINLY.

409
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:30,308
A LITTLE FOOD, A LITTLE WINE.

410
00:22:30,348 --> 00:22:32,518
VULCANS DON'T DRINK WINE.

411
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:34,061
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

412
00:22:34,103 --> 00:22:36,730
JUST HELP ME MAKE HIM GO AWAY.

413
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,529
PHLOX: WHEN DID
THESE SYMPTOMS BEGIN?

414
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:45,031
T'POL: TWO DAYS AGO.

415
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:48,117
PHLOX: HMM. PERHAPS YOU SLEPT
IN AN AWKWARD POSITION.

416
00:22:48,159 --> 00:22:50,161
T'POL: I HAVEN'T SLEPT.

417
00:22:50,203 --> 00:22:52,370
PHLOX: FOR TWO DAYS?

418
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:54,414
SOMETHING ON YOUR MIND?

419
00:22:54,456 --> 00:22:58,376
IT APPEARS TO BE
A TENSION HEADACHE.

420
00:22:58,418 --> 00:23:03,132
YOU KNOW ANYTHING SAID BETWEEN
US IS STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL.

421
00:23:03,174 --> 00:23:06,344
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TALK
ABOUT WHAT'S TROUBLING YOU?

422
00:23:06,384 --> 00:23:09,055
T'POL: NO.

423
00:23:09,096 --> 00:23:10,514
PHLOX: I DON'T KNOW IF THERE'S
ANYONE ON THIS SHIP

424
00:23:10,556 --> 00:23:12,225
YOU<i> WOULD</i> FEEL COMFORTABLE
TALKING WITH,

425
00:23:12,266 --> 00:23:13,809
BUT, UH, IF THERE IS,
IT MIGHT FEEL GOOD

426
00:23:13,851 --> 00:23:16,645
TO GET WHATEVER'S BOTHERING
YOU OUT IN THE OPEN.

427
00:23:23,401 --> 00:23:25,403
THIS IS A SIMPLE ANALGESIC.

428
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:27,114
I CAN GIVE YOU
SOMETHING LATER

429
00:23:27,156 --> 00:23:30,743
TO HELP YOU SLEEP
THIS EVENING IF YOU'D LIKE.

430
00:23:30,784 --> 00:23:32,995
T'POL: THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

431
00:23:40,418 --> 00:23:42,462
[ BEEPING ]

432
00:24:11,449 --> 00:24:14,536
TRAVIS: THE EARS
ARE A NICE TOUCH.

433
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:17,415
REED: I THOUGHT SO.

434
00:24:17,455 --> 00:24:19,499
TRAVIS: WE SHOULD
GET OUT MORE OFTEN.

435
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:22,086
REED: DON'T GET
TOO COMFORTABLE.

436
00:24:22,128 --> 00:24:25,505
THIS LANDSCAPE IS
ABOUT TO CHANGE.

437
00:24:25,547 --> 00:24:27,883
REED TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

438
00:24:27,925 --> 00:24:30,510
ARCHER: GO AHEAD.
REED: CHARGES ARE SET.

439
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:33,055
STAND BY.

440
00:24:33,097 --> 00:24:36,683
INFORM THE VULCANS WE'RE ABOUT
TO MAKE A VERY LOUD NOISE.

441
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:38,476
AYE, SIR.

442
00:24:38,518 --> 00:24:40,313
ARCHER TO REED.

443
00:24:40,354 --> 00:24:41,688
REED: YES, CAPTAIN?

444
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:43,232
BLAST AWAY.

445
00:24:43,274 --> 00:24:44,984
UNDERSTOOD.

446
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:07,381
TRAVIS: IMPRESSIVE.

447
00:25:07,423 --> 00:25:11,551
REED: EH...I WAS HOPING FOR
A LITTLE MORE SYMMETRY.

448
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,887
[ TRAVIS CHUCKLES ]
I'LL GET THE DRILL.

449
00:25:29,153 --> 00:25:30,237
ARCHER: IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN,

450
00:25:30,279 --> 00:25:33,407
YOU'RE FLYING
A SUUROK-CLASS SHIP.

451
00:25:33,449 --> 00:25:35,034
VANIK: YOU'RE NOT MISTAKEN.

452
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:38,620
ARCHER: YOU CAN GET HER UP
TO WHAT--6, 6.5?

453
00:25:38,662 --> 00:25:40,080
VANIK: 6.5.

454
00:25:40,122 --> 00:25:41,832
ARCHER: I'D LOVE TO GET A LOOK
INSIDE THOSE NACELLES.

455
00:25:41,874 --> 00:25:43,000
[ CHUCKLES ]

456
00:25:43,042 --> 00:25:46,170
VANIK: OUR WARP SYSTEMS
ARE CLASSIFIED.

457
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:51,300
ARCHER: A FEW YEARS BACK,

458
00:25:51,342 --> 00:25:55,221
I WAS A GUEST ABOARD
A MAYMORA-CLASS SHIP.

459
00:25:55,262 --> 00:25:59,016
THE<i> YARAHLA.</i> CAPTAIN TOK--
DO YOU KNOW HIM?

460
00:25:59,058 --> 00:26:00,393
VANIK: NOT PERSONALLY.

461
00:26:00,434 --> 00:26:04,146
ARCHER: OH. WE MADE A RUN
TO A DARK-MATTER NEBULA.

462
00:26:04,188 --> 00:26:06,773
I HELPED SET UP
THE GRAVITON TELESCOPE.

463
00:26:06,815 --> 00:26:08,734
MOST FUN I'VE EVER
HAD ON A SPACEWALK.

464
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:10,986
THOSE VULCAN E.V. SUITS
ARE SOMETHING ELSE--

465
00:26:11,028 --> 00:26:14,198
LIKE YOU'RE FLYING AROUND
INSIDE YOUR OWN LITTLE STARSHIP.

466
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:16,116
YOU'RE EASILY IMPRESSED.

467
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:27,336
SOMETHING WRONG
WITH YOUR POK TAR?

468
00:26:27,378 --> 00:26:29,922
NO.

469
00:26:31,715 --> 00:26:33,175
IF IT'S NOT TO YOUR LIKING,

470
00:26:33,217 --> 00:26:36,803
I'M SURE OUR CHEF
CAN PREPARE YOU SOMETHING ELSE.

471
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:38,596
I'VE ALREADY EATEN.

472
00:26:40,057 --> 00:26:42,518
HOPE YOU SAVED ROOM
FOR DESSERT.

473
00:26:52,819 --> 00:26:54,863
AFTER DINNER...

474
00:26:54,905 --> 00:26:57,615
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT LIKE
TO TAKE A LOOK AROUND.

475
00:26:57,657 --> 00:27:01,495
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> 
MAY NOT BE SUUROK-CLASS,

476
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:03,789
BUT SHE'S QUITE A SHIP.

477
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:06,166
VANIK: PERHAPS ANOTHER TIME.

478
00:27:07,460 --> 00:27:08,626
TEA?

479
00:27:08,668 --> 00:27:10,628
I ONLY DRINK WATER.

480
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:12,214
AH.

481
00:27:12,256 --> 00:27:17,052
YOU KNOW, FOR PEOPLE
WHO CLAIM TO NOT BE EXPLORERS,

482
00:27:17,094 --> 00:27:18,636
YOU SURE DO GET AROUND.

483
00:27:18,678 --> 00:27:22,516
I HOPE OUR PRESENCE HERE
IS NOT PROVING INCONVENIENT.

484
00:27:22,558 --> 00:27:23,601
ARCHER: ON THE CONTRARY,

485
00:27:23,641 --> 00:27:24,977
IT'S NICE TO KNOW

486
00:27:25,018 --> 00:27:27,146
NO MATTER HOW BIG
THE UNIVERSE IS,

487
00:27:27,187 --> 00:27:30,399
THERE'S ALWAYS
A VULCAN SHIP NEARBY.

488
00:27:32,443 --> 00:27:36,572
SO, CAPTAIN.
TELL US ABOUT YOURSELF.

489
00:27:36,614 --> 00:27:38,198
EXCUSE ME?

490
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:41,910
ON EARTH, IT'S CUSTOMARY TO
EXCHANGE PERSONAL INFORMATION

491
00:27:41,952 --> 00:27:43,661
WITH SOMEONE YOU'VE JUST MET.

492
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:48,000
WE HAVE THIS PECULIAR HABIT OF
ACTUALLY TALKING DURING MEALS.

493
00:27:48,041 --> 00:27:50,710
VANIK: I'VE NOTICED.

494
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:53,506
WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE TO KNOW?

495
00:27:53,547 --> 00:27:54,672
I DON'T KNOW.

496
00:27:54,714 --> 00:27:56,342
WHERE WERE YOU BORN?

497
00:27:56,383 --> 00:27:58,427
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN CAPTAIN?

498
00:27:58,469 --> 00:28:01,013
ANY...HOBBIES?

499
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:04,517
I'VE SERVED IN THE VULCAN
SPACE PROGRAM FOR 76 YEARS,

500
00:28:04,558 --> 00:28:07,019
15 OF THOSE
COMMANDING THE<i> TI'MUR.</i>

501
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:09,687
I BELIEVE THIS IS
CAPTAIN VANIK'S FIRST VISIT

502
00:28:09,729 --> 00:28:12,858
ABOARD AN EARTH VESSEL.

503
00:28:12,899 --> 00:28:17,821
WE'D BE HAPPY TO ANSWER
ANY QUESTIONS YOU MIGHT HAVE.

504
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:19,657
VANIK: I HAVE NONE.

505
00:28:19,697 --> 00:28:23,327
HUMANS HAVE NEVER
HELD MUCH INTEREST FOR ME.

506
00:28:28,915 --> 00:28:32,836
ARCHER: WELL,
WHERE DID THE TIME GO?

507
00:28:32,878 --> 00:28:34,963
SEEMS LIKE YOU JUST GOT HERE.

508
00:28:35,005 --> 00:28:37,341
I'M SURE YOU'RE EAGER
TO GET BACK TO YOUR SHIP,

509
00:28:37,383 --> 00:28:40,302
SO I'LL TROUBLE YOU
WITH JUST ONE LAST QUESTION.

510
00:28:40,344 --> 00:28:43,722
HOW LONG DO YOU PLAN
ON SPYING ON US?

511
00:28:43,763 --> 00:28:48,101
IF WE WERE SPYING, CAPTAIN,

512
00:28:48,143 --> 00:28:50,688
YOU WOULD'VE NEVER
DETECTED OUR PRESENCE.

513
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:53,023
YOUR INEXPERIENCE
AND YOUR ARROGANCE

514
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:55,150
ARE YOUR ENEMIES, NOT US.

515
00:29:01,574 --> 00:29:04,993
ARCHER: PLEASE SHOW CAPTAIN
VANIK TO THE LAUNCH BAY.

516
00:29:10,624 --> 00:29:14,211
[ SPEAKS VULCAN ]

517
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:18,340
WHAT'D HE SAY?

518
00:29:29,935 --> 00:29:31,478
HMM.

519
00:29:32,854 --> 00:29:35,441
HOSHI: CAPTAIN, YOU SHOULD
TAKE A LOOK AT THIS.

520
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:55,127
ARCHER: ARCHER
TO LIEUTENANT REED.

521
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:56,336
GO AHEAD, SIR.

522
00:29:56,378 --> 00:29:57,421
ARCHER: HOW'S IT GOING?

523
00:29:57,463 --> 00:29:59,047
REED: WE HIT A LAYER
OF MAGNESITE,

524
00:29:59,089 --> 00:30:01,550
AND WE'VE CRACKED A DRILL BIT,
BUT WE'VE REPLACED IT.

525
00:30:01,592 --> 00:30:03,093
ARCHER: YOU MAY WANT TO
PICK UP THE PACE A LITTLE.

526
00:30:03,135 --> 00:30:04,386
REED: SIR?

527
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:06,138
ARCHER: THE COMET'S
ROTATIONAL AXIS SHIFTED

528
00:30:06,179 --> 00:30:08,056
WHEN YOU SET OFF THOSE CHARGES.

529
00:30:08,098 --> 00:30:09,891
IN ABOUT TWO HOURS,

530
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:12,936
THE SHUTTLEPOD
WILL BE FACING THE STAR.

531
00:30:12,978 --> 00:30:15,773
THE TEMPERATURE'S GONNA SHOOT
UP BY A COUPLE HUNDRED DEGREES.

532
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:17,524
I WANT YOU OUT OF THERE
BEFORE THEN.

533
00:30:17,566 --> 00:30:19,318
REED: WE'LL BE DONE
WITH TIME TO SPARE, SIR.

534
00:30:19,359 --> 00:30:22,738
ARCHER: BE SURE YOU ARE.
ARCHER OUT.

535
00:30:27,242 --> 00:30:28,827
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

536
00:30:28,868 --> 00:30:30,287
COME IN.

537
00:30:32,414 --> 00:30:34,874
DECIDE TO TELL ME
WHAT VANIK SAID?

538
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:37,586
PLEASE SIT DOWN.

539
00:30:39,797 --> 00:30:43,509
I'VE NEVER SEEN
YOUR QUARTERS BEFORE.

540
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:45,844
COZY.

541
00:30:45,885 --> 00:30:48,054
YOU KNOW YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO HAVE AN OPEN FLAME

542
00:30:48,096 --> 00:30:49,431
ON THE SHIP.

543
00:30:49,473 --> 00:30:51,975
T'POL: I WAS GIVEN PERMISSION
FROM THE CAPTAIN.

544
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:53,769
THEY'RE FOR MEDITATION.

545
00:30:54,812 --> 00:30:58,315
SO...WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

546
00:30:58,357 --> 00:31:00,984
DR. PHLOX BELIEVES
THAT IT MIGHT HELP

547
00:31:01,026 --> 00:31:03,529
IF I WAS TO DISCUSS
MY PROBLEM

548
00:31:03,570 --> 00:31:05,823
WITH SOMEONE I FELT
COMFORTABLE CONFIDING IN.

549
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:10,160
YOU...WANT TO TALK TO<i> ME?</i>

550
00:31:11,704 --> 00:31:15,248
WELL, I, UM--

551
00:31:15,290 --> 00:31:17,334
I'M NOT SURE
I'M GONNA BE MUCH HELP.

552
00:31:17,376 --> 00:31:19,878
I MEAN, I'VE ONLY BEEN
IN 3 RELATIONSHIPS,

553
00:31:19,919 --> 00:31:21,839
AND THEY ALL WENT BUST.

554
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:25,091
ARE YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'T RATHER
TALK TO HOSHI OR ENSIGN KIMBALL?

555
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:26,259
SHE'S MARRIED.

556
00:31:26,301 --> 00:31:28,470
YOU WERE FAR FROM
MY FIRST CHOICE,

557
00:31:28,512 --> 00:31:30,889
BUT SPEAKING WITH SOMEONE ELSE

558
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:35,435
WOULD MEAN MORE PEOPLE
KNOWING ABOUT MY SITUATION.

559
00:31:35,477 --> 00:31:39,105
I'LL DO ANYTHING I CAN.
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

560
00:31:39,147 --> 00:31:40,899
T'POL: YOU READ THE LETTER.

561
00:31:40,940 --> 00:31:41,900
TUCKER: YES.

562
00:31:41,941 --> 00:31:43,235
T'POL: THEN YOU KNOW

563
00:31:43,276 --> 00:31:45,529
THAT UNLESS I LEAVE
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> IMMEDIATELY,

564
00:31:45,571 --> 00:31:47,989
MY WEDDING PLANS
WILL BE CANCELED.

565
00:31:49,032 --> 00:31:51,201
HAVE YOU TALKED TO...

566
00:31:51,243 --> 00:31:52,578
T'POL: KOSS.

567
00:31:52,619 --> 00:31:54,705
TUCKER: HAVE YOU TALKED TO KOSS
ABOUT ALL THIS?

568
00:31:54,747 --> 00:31:56,790
T'POL: WE HAVEN'T SPOKEN
IN MANY YEARS.

569
00:31:56,832 --> 00:32:01,336
MARRIAGES ON VULCAN
ARE ARRANGED DURING CHILDHOOD.

570
00:32:01,378 --> 00:32:04,798
I'VE ONLY MET KOSS 4 TIMES.

571
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,426
HOW CAN YOU BE IN LOVE WITH
A GUY YOU'VE ONLY MET 4 TIMES?

572
00:32:07,467 --> 00:32:09,469
IT'S ASSUMED THAT
WE'D EVENTUALLY DEVELOP

573
00:32:09,511 --> 00:32:11,346
AN AFFECTION FOR ONE ANOTHER.

574
00:32:11,388 --> 00:32:16,101
SO HIS PARENTS SEND YOU
AN ULTIMATUM?

575
00:32:16,142 --> 00:32:17,895
HE DOESN'T HAVE A SAY?

576
00:32:17,936 --> 00:32:21,398
HIS PARENTS PLANNED THE UNION.
IT'S THEIR DECISION.

577
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,982
BOY.

578
00:32:23,024 --> 00:32:25,944
WHERE I COME FROM,
ARRANGED MARRIAGES

579
00:32:25,985 --> 00:32:27,153
WENT OUT WITH SLAVERY.

580
00:32:27,195 --> 00:32:29,155
T'POL: ARE YOU GOING
TO GIVE ME ADVICE

581
00:32:29,197 --> 00:32:32,117
OR CRITICIZE
MY PEOPLE'S TRADITION?

582
00:32:32,158 --> 00:32:33,744
I'M STILL A LITTLE FUZZY
ON WHY THEY THREATENED

583
00:32:33,786 --> 00:32:35,287
TO CALL IT OFF
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

584
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:38,373
T'POL: THE CEREMONY WAS SUPPOSED
TO TAKE PLACE NEXT WEEK.

585
00:32:38,415 --> 00:32:40,959
WHEN I DECIDED TO
REMAIN ON<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>

586
00:32:41,000 --> 00:32:42,920
I REQUESTED A POSTPONEMENT.

587
00:32:42,961 --> 00:32:46,005
KOSS' PARENTS WERE INSULTED
THAT I WOULD PUT OFF OUR PLANS

588
00:32:46,047 --> 00:32:49,175
TO SERVE ON A HUMAN VESSEL.

589
00:32:49,217 --> 00:32:50,803
WELL, VANIK CAN TAKE YOU HOME.

590
00:32:50,844 --> 00:32:53,806
WHY DON'T YOU GO MARRY KOSS,
THEN COME BACK?

591
00:32:53,847 --> 00:32:55,557
T'POL: IT'S CUSTOMARY
FOR A HUSBAND AND WIFE

592
00:32:55,599 --> 00:32:58,936
TO RESIDE TOGETHER FOR
AT LEAST ONE VULCAN YEAR.

593
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,395
TUCKER: MAYBE HE CAN COME
TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

594
00:33:00,437 --> 00:33:01,980
T'POL: HE'S AN ARCHITECT.

595
00:33:02,021 --> 00:33:04,566
IT WOULD BE ILLOGICAL FOR HIM
TO LIVE ABOARD A STARSHIP.

596
00:33:04,608 --> 00:33:07,986
THIS WHOLE THING
SOUNDS ILLOGICAL.

597
00:33:08,027 --> 00:33:10,906
YOUR ADVICE, COMMANDER.

598
00:33:10,948 --> 00:33:14,409
WHAT DO<i> YOU</i> WANT TO DO?

599
00:33:14,451 --> 00:33:16,620
THAT IS IRRELEVANT.

600
00:33:16,662 --> 00:33:18,997
NO, IT'S NOT.
IT'S VERY RELEVANT.

601
00:33:19,038 --> 00:33:21,541
DO YOU WANT TO GO BACK
AND MARRY THIS GUY,

602
00:33:21,583 --> 00:33:24,294
SPEND A YEAR WITH HIM,
10 YEARS, 100 YEARS,

603
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:27,046
OR DO YOU WANT TO STAY
ON<i> ENTERPRISE?</i>

604
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:29,424
I HAVE AN OBLIGATION.

605
00:33:29,466 --> 00:33:31,384
YOU'VE GOT AN OBLIGATION
TO YOURSELF.

606
00:33:31,426 --> 00:33:33,470
YOU'VE SPENT THE LAST YEAR
AROUND HUMANS.

607
00:33:33,512 --> 00:33:35,013
IF THERE'S ONE THING
YOU SHOULD'VE LEARNED,

608
00:33:35,054 --> 00:33:37,307
IT'S THAT WE'RE FREE
TO MAKE OUR OWN DECISIONS.

609
00:33:37,349 --> 00:33:39,392
THERE'S A LOT TO BE SAID
FOR PERSONAL CHOICE.

610
00:33:39,434 --> 00:33:40,978
IF YOU'D SPENT
THE LAST YEAR ON VULCAN,

611
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:43,396
YOU WOULD'VE LEARNED THAT
OUR COMMITMENT TO TRADITION

612
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:45,231
OUTWEIGHS PERSONAL CHOICE.

613
00:33:45,273 --> 00:33:47,025
I RESPECT YOUR CUSTOMS,

614
00:33:47,066 --> 00:33:50,403
BUT THIS MARRIAGE WAS ARRANGED
WHEN YOU WERE A KID.

615
00:33:50,445 --> 00:33:52,990
A LOT'S HAPPENED SINCE THEN.
PEOPLE CHANGE.

616
00:33:53,031 --> 00:33:54,240
VULCANS DON'T.

617
00:33:54,282 --> 00:33:55,784
REALLY?

618
00:33:55,826 --> 00:33:59,245
MY OBLIGATION IS TO MY CULTURE,
MY HERITAGE.

619
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:02,666
IT HAS TO TAKE PRECEDENCE.

620
00:34:02,708 --> 00:34:04,042
[ SIGHS ]

621
00:34:04,083 --> 00:34:07,671
SOUNDS TO ME LIKE YOU ALREADY
MADE UP YOUR MIND.

622
00:34:07,713 --> 00:34:10,048
WHY THE HELL
DID YOU ASK ME HERE?

623
00:34:10,089 --> 00:34:12,634
IT WAS A MISTAKE.

624
00:34:12,676 --> 00:34:14,553
I APOLOGIZE.

625
00:34:20,183 --> 00:34:21,393
TUCKER: DID IT EVER
OCCUR TO YOU

626
00:34:21,434 --> 00:34:22,936
THAT YOU MIGHT'VE
POSTPONED THE WEDDING

627
00:34:22,978 --> 00:34:25,480
BECAUSE SUBCONSCIOUSLY
YOU WANTED TO GET OUT OF IT?

628
00:34:25,522 --> 00:34:28,066
THAT WOULD IMPLY
THAT MY SUBCONSCIOUS MIND

629
00:34:28,107 --> 00:34:29,860
CONTROLS MY DECISIONS.

630
00:34:29,902 --> 00:34:31,277
IT DOESN'T.

631
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:32,445
[ SIGHS ]

632
00:34:32,487 --> 00:34:35,032
WELL, IT HAPPENS TO HUMANS
ALL THE TIME.

633
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:38,117
MAYBE YOU'RE PICKING UP
SOME OF OUR BAD HABITS.

634
00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:01,600
TRAVIS: AAH!

635
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:02,642
REED: TRAVIS!

636
00:35:02,684 --> 00:35:04,394
[ TRAVIS GROANS ]

637
00:35:07,940 --> 00:35:11,777
I'M OKAY.

638
00:35:11,818 --> 00:35:14,112
TRAVIS: OH!
REED: WHAT?

639
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:15,488
TRAVIS: MY KNEE.

640
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:18,366
REED: YOU REST HERE.

641
00:35:18,408 --> 00:35:20,118
TRAVIS: I'M ALL RIGHT.

642
00:35:20,159 --> 00:35:21,202
REED: OKAY.

643
00:35:21,244 --> 00:35:23,413
WELL, LET'S GET YOU
TO THE POD.

644
00:35:23,455 --> 00:35:25,540
I'LL COME BACK FOR THE GEAR
IF THERE'S TIME.

645
00:35:25,582 --> 00:35:27,709
TRAVIS: AT LEAST TAKE
THE CORE SAMPLE.

646
00:35:27,751 --> 00:35:29,962
WE SHOULDN'T GO BACK
TO THE SHIP EMPTY-HANDED.

647
00:35:30,003 --> 00:35:31,504
[ GROANS ]

648
00:35:42,181 --> 00:35:43,976
REED: ALMOST THERE.

649
00:35:44,017 --> 00:35:46,185
TRAVIS: IT MIGHT BE FASTER
WITHOUT THE SUITS.

650
00:35:46,227 --> 00:35:49,606
REED: YES, AND A LOT COLDER.

651
00:36:06,498 --> 00:36:09,375
[ CRACKING, RUMBLING ]

652
00:36:09,417 --> 00:36:11,628
REED: WHAT'S THAT?

653
00:36:23,222 --> 00:36:26,643
[ CRACKING, RUMBLING ]

654
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:51,710
TRAVIS: I HOPE I NEVER
SEE SNOW AGAIN.

655
00:37:21,114 --> 00:37:22,866
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

656
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:36,088
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

657
00:37:44,637 --> 00:37:46,723
REED: YOU ALL RIGHT?

658
00:37:48,641 --> 00:37:50,727
TRAVIS: WE SHOULD HAVE NEVER
IGNITED THE THRUSTERS.

659
00:37:50,769 --> 00:37:52,562
REED: WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE
WE HAD A CHOICE.

660
00:37:52,604 --> 00:37:54,606
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

661
00:38:02,321 --> 00:38:03,907
REED HERE.

662
00:38:03,949 --> 00:38:05,408
ARCHER: YOU TWO OKAY?

663
00:38:05,450 --> 00:38:08,453
MORE OR LESS.
HOW FAR DID WE DROP?

664
00:38:08,494 --> 00:38:10,747
ARCHER: ABOUT 18 METERS.
WE'LL GET YOU OUT OF THERE.

665
00:38:10,789 --> 00:38:12,415
JUST GIVE US A FEW MINUTES.

666
00:38:12,457 --> 00:38:14,500
WE'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

667
00:38:14,542 --> 00:38:16,377
BRING THE GRAPPLER ONLINE.

668
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:19,422
THE MOUTH OF THAT CHASM'S
A LITTLE NARROW.

669
00:38:19,464 --> 00:38:21,507
ARCHER: I'LL GET YOU IN
CLOSE ENOUGH.

670
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,356
DO YOU SEE THEM?

671
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:40,318
BRING US IN ANOTHER 50 METERS.

672
00:38:41,653 --> 00:38:44,114
TWO METERS STARBOARD.

673
00:38:46,491 --> 00:38:48,326
A LITTLE MORE.

674
00:38:48,367 --> 00:38:50,328
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

675
00:38:50,369 --> 00:38:53,290
THE VULCAN SHIP IS HAILING US.

676
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:54,958
TAKE A MESSAGE. I'M BUSY.

677
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:58,461
HOSHI: CAPTAIN VANIK WANTS TO
KNOW IF WE REQUIRE ASSISTANCE.

678
00:38:58,503 --> 00:39:01,339
TELL HIM WE'VE GOT
EVERYTHING UNDER CONTROL.

679
00:39:02,841 --> 00:39:06,178
THERE. RIGHT THERE.
SYNCHRONIZE TO THE ROTATION.

680
00:39:15,687 --> 00:39:18,356
ALMOST GOT IT.

681
00:39:27,490 --> 00:39:30,660
ONE HIT, ONE MISS.

682
00:39:30,702 --> 00:39:34,664
ONE'LL BE FINE. REEL THEM IN.

683
00:39:34,706 --> 00:39:36,708
[ CREAKING ]

684
00:39:41,963 --> 00:39:44,382
[ THUD ]

685
00:39:44,423 --> 00:39:46,301
THE POD'S HIT AN OUTCROPPING.

686
00:39:46,343 --> 00:39:47,426
IT'S WEDGED IN.

687
00:39:47,468 --> 00:39:49,595
TAKE US A FEW METERS TO PORT.

688
00:39:49,637 --> 00:39:51,639
WE MIGHT BE ABLE TO PULL THEM
AROUND IT.

689
00:39:56,561 --> 00:40:00,273
THOSE EISILIUM DEPOSITS
ARE DISRUPTING THE MAG LOCK.
I'M LOSING THEM.

690
00:40:00,315 --> 00:40:01,607
EASE THEM BACK DOWN.

691
00:40:07,530 --> 00:40:09,657
[ BOTH SHOUTING ]

692
00:40:09,699 --> 00:40:11,701
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

693
00:40:15,163 --> 00:40:17,332
THEY'VE FALLEN
ANOTHER 9 METERS.

694
00:40:17,374 --> 00:40:19,376
LET'S TRY IT AGAIN.

695
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:20,877
CAPTAIN, THEY'RE MOVING
OUT OF THE SUNLIGHT.

696
00:40:20,919 --> 00:40:23,088
THE SURFACE ICE
IS RECRYSTALLIZING.

697
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:25,048
IN LESS THAN AN HOUR, THAT
CHASM'LL BE SEALED UP AGAIN.

698
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:26,341
THEN WE'D BETTER HURRY.

699
00:40:26,383 --> 00:40:29,135
T'POL: THERE IS
ANOTHER OPTION--

700
00:40:29,177 --> 00:40:30,428
CAPTAIN VANIK.

701
00:40:30,469 --> 00:40:32,430
I'D RATHER LEAVE HIM
OUT OF THIS.

702
00:40:32,471 --> 00:40:33,723
HIS SHIP HAS A TRACTOR BEAM.

703
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:35,308
IT WON'T BE AFFECTED
BY THE EISILIUM.

704
00:40:35,350 --> 00:40:37,602
RESET THE GRAPPLER.

705
00:40:41,606 --> 00:40:45,443
VANIK OFFERED TO ASSIST US.
THERE'S NO SHAME IN ACCEPTING.

706
00:40:45,484 --> 00:40:48,196
ARCHER: WE CAN DO THIS
ON OUR OWN.

707
00:40:48,238 --> 00:40:50,365
TUCKER: I DON'T LIKE HIM
ANY MORE THAN YOU DO, CAPTAIN,

708
00:40:50,407 --> 00:40:53,410
BUT A TRACTOR BEAM SOUNDS LIKE
A PRETTY GOOD IDEA RIGHT NOW.

709
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:56,204
VANIK EXPECTS YOU
TO REFUSE HIS OFFER.

710
00:40:56,246 --> 00:40:59,457
HE SEES HUMANS
AS ARROGANT, PRIDEFUL.

711
00:40:59,498 --> 00:41:01,876
WHY NOT PROVE HIM WRONG?

712
00:41:01,918 --> 00:41:04,421
YOU CAN SAVE THEM,

713
00:41:04,462 --> 00:41:07,673
OR YOU CAN LET YOUR PRIDE
STAND IN THE WAY.

714
00:41:07,715 --> 00:41:09,550
YOU'RE HUMAN.

715
00:41:09,592 --> 00:41:10,927
YOU'RE FREE TO CHOOSE.

716
00:41:16,808 --> 00:41:19,518
[ RUMBLING ]

717
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:21,187
TRAVIS: THEY'VE GOT US.

718
00:41:21,229 --> 00:41:23,398
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

719
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,566
REED: GO AHEAD,<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

720
00:41:25,608 --> 00:41:28,569
VANIK: THIS IS CAPTAIN VANIK
OF THE VULCAN SHIP<i> TI'MUR.</i>

721
00:41:28,611 --> 00:41:31,614
STAND BY TO IGNITE YOUR ENGINES
AND RETURN TO YOUR SHIP.

722
00:41:45,544 --> 00:41:46,671
ARCHER: I THOUGHT YOU
MIGHT WANT TO TAKE A LOOK

723
00:41:46,712 --> 00:41:48,798
AT THE DATA WE COLLECTED.

724
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:51,509
YOU HELPED US BRING IT BACK.
IT'S THE LEAST WE CAN DO.

725
00:41:51,550 --> 00:41:53,636
<i>AS YOUR SCIENCE OFFICER</i>
<i>TOLD YOU,</i>

726
00:41:53,678 --> 00:41:55,888
<i>WE HAVE LITTLE INTEREST</i>
<i>IN COMETS.</i>

727
00:41:58,266 --> 00:42:00,810
THAT TRACTOR BEAM OF YOURS
IS QUITE SOMETHING.

728
00:42:00,852 --> 00:42:04,230
ANY CHANCE WE COULD TAKE
A LOOK AT THE SPECIFICATIONS?

729
00:42:04,272 --> 00:42:07,608
<i>THAT INFORMATION IS CLASSIFIED.</i>

730
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:09,277
I THOUGHT IT MIGHT BE.

731
00:42:09,319 --> 00:42:11,070
<i>WE'LL BE LEAVING</i>
<i>WITHIN THE HOUR.</i>

732
00:42:11,112 --> 00:42:12,947
<i>IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE</i>
<i>WE CAN HELP YOU WITH?</i>

733
00:42:15,408 --> 00:42:16,701
YOU'VE DONE MORE THAN ENOUGH.

734
00:42:18,953 --> 00:42:20,079
SEE YOU AROUND.

735
00:42:26,711 --> 00:42:27,753
TUCKER: YOU DON'T
HAVE MUCH TIME.

736
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:31,966
I ASSUME YOU'RE ALL PACKED.

737
00:42:34,302 --> 00:42:35,470
CAPTAIN?

738
00:42:35,512 --> 00:42:36,471
WITH YOUR PERMISSION,

739
00:42:36,513 --> 00:42:37,930
I'D LIKE TO TRANSMIT
A MESSAGE

740
00:42:37,972 --> 00:42:41,684
TO THE<i> TI'MUR,</i> 
TO SEND TO VULCAN.

741
00:42:41,726 --> 00:42:43,811
GO RIGHT AHEAD.

742
00:42:43,853 --> 00:42:44,854
T'POL: THANK YOU.

743
00:42:57,325 --> 00:42:59,994
ARCHER: WHAT WAS THAT
ALL ABOUT?

744
00:43:00,036 --> 00:43:01,246
TUCKER: IT'S PERSONAL.
